02/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu said Wednesday (1 December) that the country's NATO integration bid enjoys the support of all political parties, institutions and the public.
He also reaffirmed the country's commitment to continued reforms, as well as to strengthened security and stability in the region.
In other news Wednesday, Albania's Central Election Commission approved a revised plan for the division of constituencies.
The document calls for creating 100 constituencies, in order to secure equality of territory and population.
(Albanian Daily News - 02/12/04;
ATA - 01/12/04)
